00:49.400 --> 00:50.600
ARE YOU OK?

00:51.000 --> 00:53.300
PROMISE ME SOMETHING.
ANYTHING.

00:53.300 --> 00:54.600
THAT NO MATTER
HOW LONG IT TAKES,

00:54.600 --> 00:57.500
WE NEVER STOP TRYING
TO GET PREGNANT.

00:59.600 --> 01:00.600
I PROMISE.

01:00.600 --> 01:03.700
OK. EVEN AFTER WE'RE PREGNANT,
WE HAVE TO KEEP TRYING.

01:03.700 --> 01:05.500
CHECK THE FINE PRINT. I THINK
IT'S IN THE WEDDING VOWS.

01:05.500 --> 01:06.400
COME ON.

01:06.500 --> 01:08.000
DO YOU THINK
THAT DELIA NOTICED

01:08.000 --> 01:09.700
I DIDN'T HAVE ANY WINE
WITH DINNER TONIGHT?

01:09.700 --> 01:11.500
NO. I DON'T THINK
SHE DID.

01:11.500 --> 01:13.800
BUT MAYBE YOU SHOULD
TELL HER WE'RE TRYING.

01:13.800 --> 01:15.300
SHE IS YOUR BEST
FRIEND, HUH?

01:16.400 --> 01:18.400
IT'S JUST SUCH
A LETDOWN, YOU KNOW?

01:18.400 --> 01:20.300
EVERY TIME IT DOESN'T
HAPPEN, I-

01:20.300 --> 01:21.700
I DON'T WANT
TO LET HER DOWN, TOO.

01:21.700 --> 01:22.900
HEY, IT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

01:23.600 --> 01:25.300
WE'VE ONLY BEEN
TRYING 4 MONTHS.

01:26.400 --> 01:27.100
I KNOW.

01:29.200 --> 01:30.200
OH, NO.

01:31.600 --> 01:33.800
CLANCY, YEAH.

01:33.800 --> 01:35.300
RIGHT. OK.

01:35.400 --> 01:38.100
I'LL BE THERE
IN 5 MINUTES.

01:38.100 --> 01:39.600
THERE'S A MULTIPLE VICTIM
FIRE AT ROCKLAND UNIVERSITY,

01:39.600 --> 01:41.300
ONE OF THE OFFICE
BUILDINGS.

01:42.600 --> 01:44.800
DID THEY WHICH
OFFICE BUILDING?

01:44.900 --> 01:46.600
NO.

01:58.400 --> 02:00.400
Jim: HONEY, I'M GONNA GO
CHECK WITH THE COMMANDER.

02:00.500 --> 02:02.800
Melinda: EXCUSE ME,
HAVE YOU SEEN RICK PAYNE?

02:02.900 --> 02:04.500
PROFESSOR PAYNE?

02:05.200 --> 02:06.600
HEY, WHAT DO WE GOT?

02:06.700 --> 02:08.400
HAS ANYONE SEEN RICK PAYNE?

02:08.400 --> 02:11.000
I HAVE, BUT USUALLY WHEN I'M
STANDING IN FRONT OF A MIRROR.

02:11.100 --> 02:12.900
YOU'RE OK.
YEAH.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.500
I'M MORE THAN OK. I MEAN,
ASK AROUND. YOU'LL HEAR THAT-

02:14.600 --> 02:16.800
SO WHY THE HELL DIDN'T
YOU ANSWER YOUR PHONE?!

02:16.900 --> 02:19.300
MELINDA, I TALKED YOU ON
THE TELEPHONE AN HOUR AGO!

02:19.300 --> 02:20.800
I TALKED TO YOU
INSIDE MY HOME.

02:20.800 --> 02:22.700
WHAT WOULD MAKE YOU THINK
THAT I WAS IN THAT BUILDING?

02:22.700 --> 02:24.600
GET THE PADDLES
READY.

02:24.700 --> 02:26.800
OH. THE SHADOW THING.

02:26.800 --> 02:28.500
YOU THOUGHT IT WAS
A BAD OMEN, HUH?

02:28.500 --> 02:30.000
YOU THOUGHT
MY NUMBER WAS UP.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.500
BUT I'M OK.
I'M HERE.

02:31.600 --> 02:32.700
I SHOULD HAVE
CALLED YOU.

02:32.800 --> 02:33.900
THAT'S WHAT A FRIEND
WOULD HAVE DONE.

02:33.900 --> 02:35.500
A FRIEND WOULD HAVE
DONE MORE THAN THAT.

02:35.600 --> 02:37.000
Jim: CHARGING.

02:37.100 --> 02:38.900
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?
CLEAR.

02:43.900 --> 02:45.400
LET'S DO IT AGAIN.

02:45.500 --> 02:47.200
LET'S TRY 200.

02:47.300 --> 02:49.100
CLEAR.

02:52.200 --> 02:53.400
NOTHING. GIVE ME 360.

02:53.500 --> 02:54.600
Jim: CLEAR.
CLEAR.

02:58.200 --> 02:59.500
Jim: I SEE LIFE.

03:00.900 --> 03:02.100
YES, WE GOT HIM.

03:02.200 --> 03:04.400
YEAH, HE'S RESPONSIVE.

03:04.400 --> 03:06.000
I SEE LIFE.

03:06.100 --> 03:07.400
THAT'S WHAT I SEE.

03:07.500 --> 03:08.500
CHECK HIS BLOOD
PRESSURE, HUH?

03:08.500 --> 03:11.200
Man: PLEASE, HELP ME OUT.

03:13.400 --> 03:15.000
CONGRATULATIONS
ON SAVING THAT GUY.

03:15.100 --> 03:16.700
NICE JOB.
WELL DONE.

03:41.450 --> 03:42.300
HI.

03:42.400 --> 03:43.700
HOW LONG HAS THIS
BEEN GOING ON?

03:43.800 --> 03:45.800
EVER SINCE HE REGAINED
CONSCIOUSNESS.

03:45.900 --> 03:47.100
WHO IS HE?

03:47.200 --> 03:48.900
HIS NAME'S
ELI JAMES.

03:49.000 --> 03:50.400
HE'S A PSYCHOLOGY
PROFESSOR

03:50.400 --> 03:52.200
WITH A THERAPY PRACTICE
AT THE UNIVERSITY.

03:52.200 --> 03:53.600
HIS OFFICE WAS IN THE
BUILDING THAT BURNED.

03:53.700 --> 03:55.100
ARE HIS EYES OK?

03:55.200 --> 03:56.600
YEAH, IT'S JUST SWELLING
FROM THE SMOKE.

03:56.600 --> 03:57.700
HE'S FINE.

03:57.800 --> 04:00.300
HOW LONG HAS HE LIVED
IN GRANDVIEW?

04:00.400 --> 04:03.000
I DON'T KNOW. WHY?

04:09.100 --> 04:11.100
AND SO IT CAUGHT ME,
LIKE, HORRIFICALLY,

04:11.200 --> 04:12.900
AND THEN I-
HI...

04:12.900 --> 04:16.100
ELI, MY NAME
IS MELINDA GORDON.

04:16.100 --> 04:17.500
OH, UH...

04:17.600 --> 04:19.399
SORRY IF I DON'T
GET UP.

04:19.500 --> 04:20.800
THIS IS MY FRIEND FIONA.

04:20.899 --> 04:23.500
HI.

04:23.600 --> 04:25.400
NICE TO MEET YOU.

04:25.500 --> 04:26.600
SHOULD I KNOW
THAT NAME?

04:26.700 --> 04:28.200
WE'VE NEVER MET BEFORE,

04:28.300 --> 04:30.900
WHICH IS... ODD,
IN A WAY.

04:30.900 --> 04:33.100
WHY? ARE YOU IN
THE PSYCH DEPARTMENT?

04:33.100 --> 04:34.300
NO.

04:34.300 --> 04:35.700
GAMBLER'S ANONYMOUS?

04:35.800 --> 04:37.900
NO.
WAIT.

04:38.000 --> 04:40.600
IF YOU'RE THAT GIRL FROM
THE ELECTRIC SHOCK STUDY,

04:40.700 --> 04:41.700
THOSE ELECTRODES
WERE NOT SUPPOSED TO-

04:41.800 --> 04:44.100
OK, IT'S OK, ELI,

04:44.200 --> 04:47.000
I UNDERSTAND. I...

04:47.100 --> 04:48.800
I CAN TALK TO THEM, TOO.

04:48.900 --> 04:50.100
TALK TO WHO?

04:50.200 --> 04:52.100
GHOSTS.

04:55.500 --> 04:57.000
IF YOU WORK
IN THE HOSPITAL,

04:57.100 --> 05:00.000
THIS IS DEFINITELY NOT
POST-TRAUMA COUNSELING PROTOCOL.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.700
NO ONE TOLD YOU.
TOLD ME WHAT?

05:01.700 --> 05:04.700
YOU KNOW WHAT,
IT'S REALLY BETTER IF I-

05:04.700 --> 05:06.300
TOLD ME WHAT?

05:08.600 --> 05:11.200
ELI, FIONA DIED

05:11.200 --> 05:13.100
IN THAT FIRE WITH YOU.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.800
THEY COULDN'T BRING HER BACK,
I'M SO SORRY.

05:24.800 --> 05:25.900
WHERE'S FIONA?

05:26.000 --> 05:27.500
I JUST TOLD YOU.

05:29.122 --> 05:30.200
SHE'S DEAD.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.100
THEN WHO WAS I
TALKING TO?

05:34.200 --> 05:36.900
YOU WERE TALKING
TO HER GHOST.

